              "score": 1.0,
              "correctreply": "Parents and children go through a number of stages as they learn and grow together. This learning and growing is often somewhat painful. Parents, in particular, are often stricken by the sadness of dealing with children who are struggling for their own identity. However, given the common direction of parent-child relationships, it's surprising that people are weakened by it, surprising that they worry so much, and surprising that they are upset by it at all.<br>When pregnant, a mother-to-be imagines many good things that will happen for her child. She and her husband will give the child as much as possible to try to make these good things come about. Usually, all of this giving leads to the child being spoiled and selfish. However, the child grows out of this gradually and in time.<br>As they reach adulthood, children become more sensitive to the needs of others, including their parents. They uncover, through a process of discovery, the need to make continual improvements in life.<br>The relationship between parents and children can be the most rewarding relationship of one's life, so long as both sides expect the fluctuations in it. The experience of most people shows that parents usually end up being the best friends that their children ever had.<br><p>Q 10: Why is a parent-child relationship so surprising?</p><p>Q 11: What does a woman imagine before her child is born?</p>Q 12: Often, what is the result of all the giving done by the parents?<br>Q 13: What happens to make children understand the need to become better people?<br>Q 14: How can parents and children find their relationship more rewarding?<br>",
